<taxonomicName id="6981899A7260F3CC8588A0834530086E" family="Asteraceae" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. diantherae" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="diantherae">
<emphasis id="1E33CE1D4B5279F4BE7E81F26EA385D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. diantherae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are superficially similar, being large and stout-bodied with a blue metallic shine and more than five fronto-orbital setae. The two species are otherwise quite different in both outward and genitalic morphology, and can be easily diagnosed using the characters listed in the key.
</paragraph>
